description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a well organised and self-motivated individual to work within the IT Service Delivery function of Buckinghamshire Healthcare NHS Trust&#39;s IT department, based in Aylesbury. The Trust covers Amersham, Wycombe and Stoke Mandeville Hospitals as well as numerous health clinics and community sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to work as part of the Server Team to provide technical support for the many and diverse servers and systems that are supported by the Trust’s IT department. Support will be carried out in accordance with the appropriate Service Level Agreements, as well as departmental guidelines and policies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also provide additional help and support to the rest of the IT Department to resolve technical incidents, minimise risks and provide an extensive and efficient service to colleagues across the Trust as well as to external customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should have knowledge and experience in the following technologies:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Microsoft Windows Server (including Active Directory, Group Policy, file and print services, DNS, DHCP, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing virtual servers through VMware vSphere and related technologies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should also have experience in at least some of the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other Microsoft server technologies (e.g. SQL, IIS, RDS)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Server hardware configuration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enterprise backup software&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Server and endpoint security&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should ideally have experience of supporting Windows servers in a business or enterprise virtualised environment, with strong problem solving and troubleshooting skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;John Upstone, IT Infrastructure Delivery Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;john.upstone@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 07979 802239&lt;/p&gt;
